  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<ul><li>Initiation: Defining project purpose, goals, and feasibility; identifying stakeholders; and creating the project charter.</li></ul><ul><li>Planning: Developing comprehensive roadmaps, setting realistic timelines (using tools like Gantt charts), and establishing budgets and resource allocation plans.</li></ul><ul><li>Execution: Coordinating team members, assigning tasks, and facilitating daily operations to ensure work meets the project plan.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitoring & Controlling: Tracking progress against KPls, managing budgets, mitigating risks, and implementing necessary changes (handling \"scope creep\")</li></ul><ul><li>Closing: Obtaining formal stakeholder sign-off, releasing resources, and conducting post-project evaluations to document lessons learned.</li></ul><ul><li>Must be able to <strong>speak, read,</strong> and<strong> write</strong> <strong>Mandarin</strong> to communicate with Mandarin-speaking stakeholders.</li></ul><ul><li>Able to travel.</li></ul>",
